**who —** LUCA — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind

**what —** Trace every living thing — every microbe, mushroom, redwood, octopus, and human — back far enough, and the branches meet at a single point: one population of cells, some four billion years ago, from which all life descends. Not the first life, but the last ancestor we all share. The single trunk beneath the entire tree.

